'''Zey Nep''' was a [[Gender/Legends|female]] [[Human/Legends|Human]] who served as an assistant to [[Artuo Pratuhr]], an [[Archaeologist/Legends|archaeologist]] working for the [[Galactic Museum/Legends|Galactic Museum]]. In [[22 BBY/Legends|22 BBY]], she was a frequent vistor of the [[Outlander Club/Legends|Outlander Club]] on [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]]. She was often found with her friends [[Dixon Just]] and [[Civ Sila]].<ref name="zn" /> After Pratuhr was robbed of his money by a double-crossing ex-member of [[Sisterhood of the Beatific Countenance]], [[Seib Nod]], Nep helped to reclaim the money by training her [[Blaster/Legends|blaster]] upon Nod's back when Pratuhr engaged the thief in a dock from which she tried to leave Coruscant. As a result, Pratuhr got the money back and the stolen Sisterhood artifacts which Nod used to lure the archaeologist were sent back to the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Lorrd/Legends|Lorrd]].<ref name="db">{{DB|character|seibnod|Nod, Seib}}</ref>

==Behind the scenes==
Zey Nep was portrayed by [[Zeynep Selcuk|Zeynep "Zed" Selcuk]] in the [[2003|2002]] film [[Star Wars: Episode II Attack of the Clones|''Attack of the Clones'']].<ref name="Club Zed">{{SWArchive|url=episode-ii/explore/attack/2002/10/imageattack20021029.html|series=Image Attack|text=Club Zed}}</ref>

